          "text": "Employers pay 7.65% of each employee's wages in FICA taxes: 6.2% for Social Security (on wages up to $168,600 in 2024) and 1.45% for Medicare (no wage cap). This is in addition to the employee's matching 7.65% withholding. Self-employed individuals pay the full 15.3% as self-employment tax. FICA is one of the largest non-salary costs for employers."
